// §5.16.3 Collection Predicate
numbers are 1, 2, 3, 4, 5

all_positive is std.all(numbers, function n as i64 returns bool { n > 0 })
any_even is std.any(numbers, function n as i64 returns bool { n % 2 is 0 })

// empty list edge cases
vacuous is std.all([] as [i64], function n as i64 returns bool { n > 100 })
none is std.any([] as [i64], function n as i64 returns bool { n > 0 })

// with named function type
_pred is function n as i64 returns bool { n > 0 } called IntPred
check is std.all(numbers, function n as i64 returns bool { n > 0 } as IntPred)
